{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:49.639898+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4ad40d3e089c2e690280c68e60e381447c422508)", "id": "lc_a7f765dd-019d-40a7-a9d4-f2ba9b380436"}, {"type": "text", "text": "package io.dodn.springboot.storage.db;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Tag;\nimport org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\nimport org.springframework.test.context.ActiveProfiles;\nimport org.springframework.test.context.TestConstructor;\n\n@ActiveProfiles(\"local\")\n@Tag(\"context\")\n@SpringBootTest\n@TestConstructor(autowireMode = TestConstructor.AutowireMode.ALL)\npublic abstract class CoreDbContextTest {\n\n}\n", "id": "lc_4e09a3b7-fdd5-4181-9df8-6d3d2f93abf9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e52cbeab-2f69-4b1b-832b-d10f4a5e9ea3", "tool_call_id": "call_6165abeb3530417aa9911416", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:49.671197+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: c96da29dfb248601b625eb5f6f881f0edc462338)", "id": "lc_a1e185ec-3212-458f-98da-3011bfd75d72"}, {"type": "text", "text": "package io.dodn.springboot.storage.db.core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport io.dodn.springboot.storage.db.CoreDbContextTest;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ExampleRepositoryIT extends CoreDbContextTest {\n\n    private final ExampleRepository exampleRepository;\n\n    public ExampleRepositoryIT(ExampleRepository exampleRepository) {\n        this.exampleRepository = exampleRepository;\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void testShouldBeSavedAndFound() {\n        ExampleEntity saved = exampleRepository.save(new ExampleEntity(\"SPRING_BOOT\"));\n        assertThat(saved.getExampleColumn()).isEqualTo(\"SPRING_BOOT\");\n\n        ExampleEntity found = exampleRepository.findById(saved.getId()).get();\n        assertThat(found.getExampleColumn()).isEqualTo(\"SPRING_BOOT\");\n    }\n\n}\n", "id": "lc_8b012e57-5fa5-4d5f-8c8b-59bd7ff9960f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c4be24dc-58e3-4178-bc15-aa8060b1b844", "tool_call_id": "call_0f04f61680414a8aa6224dee", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:17:10.275219+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the testing organization. Here's the full explanation:\n\n---\n\n## How Testing Is Organized in T03_R02\n\n### 1. Gradle Test Suites (defined in root `build.gradle`, applied to every subproject)\n\nThe project uses the **JUnit 5 Platform** with **tag-based** test segregation. Every subproject inherits this structure via the `subprojects {}` block in the root `build.gradle`:\n\n| Suite / Target | Task Name | Tags Included | Tags Excluded | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **default `test`** | `test` | *(all)* | `develop`, `restdocs` | Runs everything except develop-only and REST-docs tests |\n| **`unitTest`** | `unitTest` | *(all)* | `develop`, `context`, `restdocs` | Fastest suite — pure unit tests, no Spring context, no docs |\n| **`contextTest`** | `contextTest` | `context` | — | Spring Boot integration tests that load an application context |\n| **`restDocsTest`** | `restDocsTest` | `restdocs` | — | Tests that generate Spring REST Docs snippets (Asciidoc) |\n| **`developTest`** | `developTest` | `develop` | — | Developer-only / experimental tests |\n\nAll five targets live under `group = 'verification'`.\n\n### 2. The JUnit Tags Used\n\n- **`@Tag(\"context\")`** — Annotates abstract base test classes that boot a `@SpringBootTest` context (e.g. `CoreDbContextTest`). Concrete integration tests like `ExampleRepositoryIT` extend these bases and are therefore picked up by `contextTest`.\n- **`@Tag(\"restdocs\")`** — Annotates abstract base test classes that configure `MockMvc` with Spring REST Docs (e.g. `RestDocsTest`). Concrete controller tests extend them and produce Asciidoc API documentation snippets.\n- **`@Tag(\"develop\")`** — Used by tests a developer runs locally but that should never block CI.\n\n### 3. CI-Oriented vs. Develop-Only Test Execution\n\n#### CI pipeline (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)\n\n```yaml\n- name: Lint\n  arguments: checkFormat\n- name: Test\n  arguments: test\n```\n\nThe CI runs the **default `test`** task, which **excludes `develop` and `restdocs` tags**. This means:\n\n- ✅ All **unit tests** (no tag, or any tag other than `develop`/`restdocs`) run in CI.\n- ✅ All **`context`-tagged** integration tests run in CI.\n- ❌ **`develop`-tagged** tests are **skipped** in CI — they are developer-only.\n- ❌ **`restdocs`-tagged** tests are **skipped** in CI via the `test` task (they are run separately through the `restDocsTest` task, which is a dependency of the `asciidoctor` task that generates the API documentation).\n\n#### Developer workflow\n\nA developer can selectively run:\n\n| Command | What runs |\n|---|---|\n| `./gradlew test` | All tests except `develop` and `restdocs` (same as CI) |\n| `./gradlew unitTest` | Only pure unit tests (excludes `context`, `develop`, `restdocs`) |\n| `./gradlew contextTest` | Only `@Tag(\"context\")` Spring context tests |\n| `./gradlew restDocsTest` | Only `@Tag(\"restdocs\")` REST documentation tests |\n| `./gradlew developTest` | Only `@Tag(\"develop\")` developer-only tests |\n| `./gradlew asciidoctor` | Generates Asciidoc docs (auto-triggers `restDocsTest` first) |\n\n### 4. Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **`develop` tests never touch CI** — they are excluded from the default `test` task and have no dedicated CI step, so they are purely for local developer convenience.\n2. **`restdocs` tests generate documentation** — they are excluded from the default `test` task to keep CI fast, but are chained into the `asciidoctor` task so API docs are produced when needed.\n3. **`context` tests are included in CI** — unlike `develop` and `restdocs`, context-tagged tests run in CI as part of the default `test` task, ensuring integration-level correctness is verified on every push/PR.\n4. **`unitTest` target is the fastest feedback loop** — by excluding all three tags (`develop`, `context`, `restdocs`), it runs only lightweight, no-context tests.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1050, "prompt_tokens": 12445, "total_tokens": 13495, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11904, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0011916894, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002781894, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0009135}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863409-igw3tK8Lmd8II2b2pJq8", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3bb-1e07-72f2-937f-96565fec066a-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12445, "output_tokens": 1050, "total_tokens": 13495, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11904}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 17}}}}]}}}
